<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" dir="ltr">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <style type="text/css">
      body {
        background-image: url("https://i.imgur.com/TQeq5ec.png");
        color: black;
        list-style: none;
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 30px;
        color: black;
      }
      h1 {
        text-align: center;
        font-family: Palatino;
        font-style: italic;
        font-size: 40px;
      }
      h2 {
        text-align: center;
        font-family: Palatino;
        font-size: 30px;
        text-decoration: underline;
      }
      h3 {
        text-align: center;
        font-family: Palatino;
        font-size: 18px;
      }
      h4 {
        font-style: italic;
      }
      h5 {
        text-align: center;
        font-family: Palatino;
        font-size: 28px;
      }
      img {
        border-radius: 35%
      }
    </style>
    <title></title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1><span>@OhMyMycophile</span><h1>
    <%JSON.stringify(allMushrooms);%>
      <h5><span>"All fungi are edible. Some fungi are only edible once." -Terry Pratchett</span></h5>
        <h6><span>(...no but in all seriousness there's 10,000 kinds of fungi and only like 30 are edible so please don't pull a Terry Pratchett just for kicks)</span></h6>
          <h3><span>Whether you're an experienced forager or just beginning your foraging journey, remember to respect the earth you walk on. As always, take precautionary measures when foraging by adhering to local laws and guidelines. Rule of thumb: only forage with a professional or experienced mushroom forager (you can find some great foraging groups <a href="https://www.meetup.com/topics/mycology/">here</a>!) and if you are unsure, DO NOT risk it. For inquiries, <a href="https://namyco.org/clubs.php">consult with your local mycological association</a>. Have fun connecting back to the land and be safe! We can't wait to hear all about your finds! -the OMM team </span></h3>
          <h3><span>Interested in our favorite mushroom picks for beginners? Read on! (...and keep scrolling for special recipe features at the end!) </span></h3>
          <nav>
          <a href="/mushrooms/new">Create a New Mushroom</a>
          </nav>
            <h2>An Amateur's Guide to Popularly Foraged Fungi</h2>

                <% for (let i = 0; i < allMushrooms.length; i++) { %>
                  <div>
                    <h4><%=allMushrooms[i].name%></h4>

                    <a href="/mushrooms/<%=allMushrooms[i]._id%>"><img src="<%=allMushrooms[i].img%>"/></a>


                  </div>
        <% } %>

  </body>
</html>
